# Git commit messages

When the user asks to create a git commit:

- Write the **subject and body in English**, using clear and appropriate wording.
- Keep messages **concise** — state the why/purpose in 1–2 sentences; avoid long or overly detailed explanations.
- Follow the repository's existing commit message style when present.
